reviews.text: This is a really outstanding art museum. The architecture is a little outdated and feels odd on the campus, but it’s definitely standing out. Inside the museum I’m not in love with the layout. It’s very easy to get lost in the maze and the stairwells are weird. But that’s all perfectly okay because the range and quality of the art is incredible! After a few hours I’m still wanting to stick around a revisit a few pieces.

I love it! Worth every bit of the travel out here from Ohio. If you are planning to go, make sure you set aside at least a few hours. As for me, I could have spent the whole day! There is so much to learn and experience there, truly amazing. I will be returning the next chance I get!

What a delightful way to spend a beautiful Sunday morning. The "Moon" exhibit alone is worthwhile. There is more stuff that we want to see, so we'll return. The view from the 5th floor windows is spectacular.

My wife and I enjoyed this relatively small but beautiful museum. It has a diverse collection for a free experience. The deck outside the second floor is a must. You will see what I mean when you go.
Admission is free. Parking is limited. Combine the museum with a short walk across the road to the Cornell suspension bridge to get a wonderful view of the gorge and waterfall
Awesome free museum. Worth checking out for sure.

My favorite sub in the area "The Bomber" - It's basically a Cheese steak and a Buffalo chicken in one sub.  A couple places in the area make something similar, but Rogan's is the best.  They deliver all around Ithaca and have a nice online ordering system that's pretty easy to add too much stuff (they have a very nice convenience store inside and will deliver anything in it).  Always friendly staff and great togo drink options.  Also the only gas station I've been to that has beer on tap.  So if you want, they have some tables and you can have your sub or pizza with a beer right there.  They even have a couple of TV's and can have a spontaneous crowd watching a game and having a beer (kind of an odd site for inside a gas station the first time you see it.

We ordered our usual xl Bomber & Boneless Cajun wings.  When we picked up our food we noticed that the container for the wings was 1/2 the size.  We opened it at the counter to find 1 Cajun boneless chicken wing cut up into pieces.  We questioned this and was told that the district manager had ruled that this is now how boneless chicken wing orders will be.  Okay....but the price is $8.50, 2 weeks ago we  ordered the exact same thing and we had received 6 Cajun chicken wings or as they call them now Cajun chicken tenders for the same price of $8.50.  We have been using this establishment for several years in fact this was our go to, as the food was reasonably priced and very tasty. Unfortunately we won't be back.  The customer service is great and I felt bad for the workers as they had been very apologetic and slightly embarrassed.

Our pizza wasn't bad, but everything at this place felt off and nothing like what we used to get from Rogan's. Staff was off and confused as to where my order was. They seemed surprised when I was asking to pick it up. The dough was thin and we think under proofed. Our cheese pizza was pail and kinda odd looking. Now I have to be honest, I have pretty low expectations of pizza in Ithaca. So even with the flaws, the pizza tasted alright, but I am not sure we will be back anytime soon.

Amazing that our 32 years' experience of great service, nice drivers, good chefs, and outstanding food at Rogan's could be ruined in a mere 6 months by Dandy Mini Mart!! We feel sorry for the staff who have not yet found other opportunities - it can't feel good to work on a sinking ship :(  Good-bye Rogan's Corner

Rogans Corner use to be one of the best parts of Ithaca. Now thanks to Dandy this place now sucks. Prices have gone up and quality has gone down. Drivers are few and far between and the wait is often more than an hour when it use to be 20 minutes. Good job Dandy you are incompetent and have ruined an Icon of Ithaca.

As soon as you walk in it’s like stepping into real authentic southern dining - the staff is warm and friendly greeting you with smiles. The food is amazing full of great flavors that dance on your tongue. Great music cascades the atmosphere really making the dining experience top notch. Will definitely be back
Very fun place to hang and eat.  Excellent oyster bar with half price specials during happy hour. Wide selection of food include vegetarian meals.
Best seafood in town. Live music. 2$ Kids Wednesdays are great to not break a family buck.
Good atmosphere. Even on a busy Friday night the service was fast and friendly. It's a very unique environment and a must go to when in the area.

One of our favorite restaurants in Ithaca. The oysters are always fresh n tasty. Have had almost all of the menu at one time or another. Everything is great. The tuna steak on horseadish mashed potato cake is awesome. Daily specials too.

Delicious vegetarian food!! The cauliflower pasta is absolutely delightful. The portions are huge. I had food for two days. Also, the service is amazing. Our waitress was so kind and smiley. I would come back if I'd live in Ithaca.

Food is always delicious. We drive about two hours once or twice a year to  enjoy the cuisine. We appreciate the menu is made based on what is readily availabile and it is always fresh. Service is a bit slow and portions aren't huge, but the dishes are always top notch.

We love this place! The food is always wonderful, their new selections are fantastic and the staff is always great. Highly recommend the lemon tahini dressing along with a side of the ginger miso (; you'll thank me later. Also recommend the Moosewood specialty tea of juiced citrus, ginger and honey. So good!
Enjoyed the Mapo Tofu, unfortunately I was too full fit dessert. Had reservation for 5:30 when restaurant opens for dinner. Seated promptly, with 3 other people in party. Everyone enjoyed the food

Crazy Philly vegan doing an extended weekend trip to Ithaca, NY. I was extremely apprehensive to try this place as Philly had so many amazing vegan spots. This is a very hearty, home-style cooking versus vegan junk food type of spot. After dining, one feels satisfied with not just the food but also the cozy dining experience and amazing service.

Just gotta say that, in my humble opinion, this is, with out a doubt, the best Thai restaurant in Boise. Their red curry with beef is excellent. The vegetables are crisp and colorful. The red curry has just the right amount of kick, not overpowering, nor understated. My favorite is the Pad Thai! We usually order the chicken and add prawns. So often the prawns can be completely overcooked and rubbery, but not here! They are PERFECTLY cooked.
It's definitely worth the drive from downtown... that is, if you want great Thai. :-)
Great food. Very authentic. Flavors were great with all the food I have had here. Very quick service. Lunch hour is their busiest time. Price is right on and very large portions.

I absolutely love their food! My favorite dishes are the basil fried rice and drunken noodle. Don't get me wrong their food is out of this world, but the last few times that I ordered the basil fried rice it has been a bit bland and dry. Every time I ordered it, it was delicious but now maybe their is a new chef? I don't know but I am still a regular because their food is the best! Definitely recommend.

Great little restaurant. Four of us went, and we all loved the amazing food. Our server, Jaa, was great! Very helpful with pronunciations, and knowing how spicy each dish would be. We did not have reservations, but were able to get in with less than five minutes wait, even though they were pretty busy with a large party coming in. The parking can be a little tight toward the back.

One of the best Thai food joints in Boise! I frequent this place and they've got friendly staff. Food is a little pricey though. Thai is always a great option when you have many vegetarian friends. I'd definitely suggest this place to friends!

I typically do not write reviews. But in this case I have to. I order from here quite frequently. And in the past two days I spent $40 here. And today I was severely disappointed. First the order arrived and had spices on it. I can’t eat spicy food, so I called. The guy who answered seemed annoyed and asked what I wanted them to do. I was like fix it. He then put me on hold for five minutes and said it would be an hour. An hour?  So it arrived and it looked nothing like what I normally order. It was red and the portion looked smaller. So, I don’t deserve fresh correct portioned food?  Do not only did I have to wait two hours for my lunch, I spent $20 on food I can’t and won’t eat. Get it right..

Thai Express do have good food that is very affordable. However there not consistent. They have gave. 4 out of 10 times I order something there, it would be the wrong things I ordered, or prepared very poorly. Same thing happen last night. When I ordered the spinach and peanut sauce with chicken. On the ticket it clearly said chicken but somehow they gave me some nasty tofu instead. So I call them and no one can explain to me why this happened. If you buy food from this place make sure you go to pick it up and ALWAYS CHECK YOUR FOOD BEFORE YOU LEAVE. I also think that the people up front should check the food before sending it out.

The most amazing Thai place I have ever been to. This place makes the food as spicy as you want and it's delicious. Not a long wait time. Waitress was very good. If you are in Ithaca and want spicy food come here!!!
Good portion size, got the pad Thai and it was excellent! Spice rack helped get it to my level of "hot". Would definitely go back.
Hungry for Thai? This place is casual dining at its best. Food is great and the service is fast.
they have a nice selection of dishes for the lunch buffet for about $13. filling, tasty, and a good value for the price. decor is dated but the place is clean and the staff is friendly

While I lived in Ithaca this was my go-to Indian food dine-in location. The food is phenomenal and the staff is very nice. It can take a minute for the food to get to the table but it's all worth the intense flavors and satisfaction.
Best indian food I have ever had! Seriously amazing and the employees are super nice and the place has a great mellow vibe. Love it and can’t wait to go back 🤙
I always have a good experience at Diamonds! The people are wonderful and friendly. The food is delicious, well spiced, and reasonably priced.
This place is great for excellent India food. If you are looking for ambiance or decor it's not here. The food is great and the service was fast and friendly.

Had a great time.  Good food and fun staff.  Sat at bar with the chefs.  Enjoyed the scallop and mussel appetizers.  Both were well prepared, nicely presented and were delicious.  Enjoyed some nice wine and draft beers as well.  Service definetly paid attention to the details.  Was refreshkng. Go and enjoy!
The very best. Great music, nice atmosphere. delicious coffee, well matched wine.very good for vegetarians.some of the best food for the price downtown.
Scallops and seafood are excellent. Better steak at Price Chopper. We're picky though with food b/c we normally can't find a restaurant that cooks as well as we.
Perhaps the best food I've eaten, plus a hip atmosphere.  The chefs are pure talent.
Cozy little place. Very high prices. Food was not super special. The steak was different in flavor. The service was excellent! I may never go again. ? Stopped in before going to a show in town.
That was the most tender and delicious streak I've had in a long time. Romantic and friendly service. You can't go wrong.

Fantastic service. The waiters are wonderful and polite professional and friendly. Not to mention infeasible well knowledged on the food. And the food itself..... Best stake I've ever had. Must go place in Ithaca.
One of the best steaks ever! Aged meat! Yummy! ...we ate at an exclusive steakhouse last June in NYC and we both believe this was a better steak! Well done!

My rule of thumb for eating out is: If I'm going to spend money at a restaurant, the food must be better than I can make at home. Was utterly disappointed in the John Thomas Steakhouse. For those kinds of prices, I expect to be mind blown, but it was only "meh." I won't go back again. The servers did a great job though.

Zaza's is great for a special dinner or just in general. The New Zealand lamb rack is always my go to entree and it is always cooked to perfection. If you order medium, it comes out medium, if you order rare, it comes out rare, etc. The kitchen really knows what they are doing. The desserts are always top notch and the service is great. Everyone is always so nice and helpful and make you feel at home.

Not much I can say other than EXCELLENT! The waitress was phenomenal and made sure we were constantly tended to, the food was AMAZING! I ordered the Seafood Risotto, which turned out to be absolutely phenomenal. Highly recommend this for anyone looking for a fancy date night. :)

While the food was tasty, management on the other hand would get zero stars if I could.
Our son ordered plain pasta with cheese. The portion was so small that we asked if it was the appetizer. The check came and we were charged $20 for that pasta. I asked to speak to the manager. The owner was "too busy" to come to our table. The restaurant was far from full. The owner apparently asked our server to talk to the person at the bar, who took off $4. I still can't believe they think $16 is appropriate for an appetizer size portion on plain pasta with cheese. We paid and left. We will NEVER eat there again. I want to make sure no one else gets ripped off there too.

My wife and I spent our anniversary in Ithica and dinner here was a great choice.  We made a reservation online with anniversary as the occasion and they made it a little extra special for us.  Dinner was amazing.  Trust the chef and get the special.

My wife had lobster ravioli and I had strip steak. Both delicious; steak perfectly medium rare and very tender.  Special appetizer of smoked brie with peaches and arugula was wonderful.  Great evening.
